title: Google\Cloud\DataLabeling\V1beta1\EvaluationJob
name: EvaluationJob
description:
Defines an evaluation job that runs periodically to generate [Evaluations][google.cloud.datalabeling.v1beta1.Evaluation]. Creating an evaluation job is the starting point for using continuous evaluation.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.datalabeling.v1beta1.EvaluationJob

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. After you create a job, Data Labeling Service assigns a name to the job with the following format: "projects/{project_id}/evaluationJobs/{evaluation_job_id}"

params.name: data.description
params.description: Required. Description of the job. The description can be up to 25,000 characters long.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. Describes the current state of the job.

params.name: data.schedule
params.description: Required. Describes the interval at which the job runs. This interval must be at least 1 day, and it is rounded to the nearest day. For example, if you specify a 50-hour interval, the job runs every 2 days. You can provide the schedule in crontab format or in an English-like format. Regardless of what you specify, the job will run at 10:00 AM UTC. Only the interval from this schedule is used, not the specific time of day.

params.name: data.model_version
params.description: Required. The AI Platform Prediction model version to be evaluated. Prediction input and output is sampled from this model version. When creating an evaluation job, specify the model version in the following format: "projects/{project_id}/models/{model_name}/versions/{version_name}" There can only be one evaluation job per model version.

params.name: data.evaluation_job_config
params.description: Required. Configuration details for the evaluation job.

params.name: data.annotation_spec_set
params.description: Required. Name of the [AnnotationSpecSet][google.cloud.datalabeling.v1beta1.AnnotationSpecSet] describing all the labels that your machine learning model outputs. You must create this resource before you create an evaluation job and provide its name in the following format: "projects/{project_id}/annotationSpecSets/{annotation_spec_set_id}"

params.name: data.label_missing_ground_truth
params.description: Required. Whether you want Data Labeling Service to provide ground truth labels for prediction input. If you want the service to assign human labelers to annotate your data, set this to true. If you want to provide your own ground truth labels in the evaluation job's BigQuery table, set this to false.

params.name: data.attempts
params.description: Output only. Every time the evaluation job runs and an error occurs, the failed attempt is appended to this array.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. Timestamp of when this evaluation job was created.
